{
  "doc_id": "49582",
  "text": "Although microscopy is the only method of malaria detection in hospital laboratories in Malaysia, the decrease in diagnostic discrepancy is due to the increased awareness about P. knowlesi infections among the local laboratory technicians and [CITATION_1] microscopists [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Coupled with the fact that P. malariae infections are not frequent in Malaysia, the detection of malaria parasites with morphology similar to that of P. malariae should be reported as \"P. knowlesi\" [CITATION_5] . Thereby, knowlesi malaria has been accounted for more than a half of all cases of malaria in Malaysia [CITATION_6] .",
